Description:
The miscarriage support group will provide you the opportunity to meet with others who have suffered from miscarriage in a caring and supportive environment and to discuss the challenges of coping with this loss.

Sessions will be moderated by a psychologist and a nurse specializing in miscarriage and by Dr. Zev Williams, Director of the Program for Early and Recurrent Pregnancy Loss at the Albert Einstein College of Medicine. The drop-in group will meet the first Wednesday evening of the month from 6:30-8:00 pm. 

This class is free.
ShortDesc: The miscarriage support group will provide you the opportunity to meet with others who have suffered from miscarriage in a caring and supportive environment and to discuss the challenges of coping with this loss.
Title: Miscarriage Support Group

Description:
New Boot Camp for Dads is an opportunity for expectant and new dads (and their babies) to connect with veteran dads for a frank discussion on the experience of becoming a father.

92Y’s 2015 Parenting Conference is a day dedicated to dads! Join us for Why Fathers Matter on Sun, Jan 25. Learn how a new generation is redefining fatherhood from a distinguished lineup of speakers, experts and dads, including Boot Camp for Dads’ Lance Somerfeld.

We’ll talk about the opportunities and rewards of personally caring for our children as dads demonstrate holding, burping, changing, swaddling and comforting crying babies. We'll also discuss new parent related issues including being supportive of your baby's mom, importance of fathers involvement in early childhood development, navigating work as a new parent, developing a parenting partnership, managing relatives and more.

Boot Camp for Dads is presented by NYC Dads Group, a diverse and growing community of fathers who take an active role in our children’s lives. NYC Dads Group seeks to bring fathers together in person and online as they redefine what it means to be a dad in the 21st century.

As one of the largest physical groups of dads in the United States, NYC Dads Group has been featured in local and national media including "The Today Show," Wall Street Journal, "Nightline," The New York Times, USA Today, CNN, "ABC World News Tonight," "CBS Sunday Morning," Business Week, "CBS Evening News," Parenting Magazine, NY Post, Daily News, New York Family Magazine, Time Out New York Kids and many others.

  • "At-Home Dads Make Parenting More of a 'Guy' Thing," The Wall Street Journal (Jan 2013)
  • "Stay-At-Home Dads Embrace the New Family Norm," "TODAY SHOW" (September 2012)
  • "Dads Are Taking Over as Full-Time Parents," The New York Times (August 2012)
ShortDesc: New Boot Camp for Dads is an opportunity for expectant and new dads (and their babies) to connect with veteran dads for a frank discussion on the experience of becoming a father.
Title: Boot Camp for Dads
